01:02:17,800 --> 01:02:20,790
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Then we want back the honey that was ours to begin with,

987
01:02:20,870 --> 01:02:22,490
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}every last drop.

988
01:02:22,570 --> 01:02:26,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}We demand an end to the glorification of the bear as anything more

989
01:02:26,940 --> 01:02:29,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}than a filthy, smelly, bad-breath stink machine.

990
01:02:29,940 --> 01:02:32,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}We're all aware of what they do in the woods.

991
01:02:33,610 --> 01:02:35,040
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Wait for my signal.

992
01:02:36,950 --> 01:02:38,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Take him out.

993
01:02:40,180 --> 01:02:43,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}He'll have nauseous for a few hours, then he'll be fine.

994
01:02:43,220 --> 01:02:46,660
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}And we will no longer tolerate bee-negative nicknames...

995
01:02:46,720 --> 01:02:48,660
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}But it's just a prance-about stage name!

996
01:02:48,730 --> 01:02:52,060
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}...unnecessary inclusion of honey in bogus health products

997
01:02:52,130 --> 01:02:56,290
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}and la-dee-da human tea-time snack garnishments.

998
01:02:57,870 --> 01:02:59,130
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Can't breathe.

999
01:03:01,640 --> 01:03:02,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Bring it in, boys!

1000
01:03:04,980 --> 01:03:07,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Hold it right there! Good.

1001
01:03:08,580 --> 01:03:10,480
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Tap it.

1002
01:03:14,090 --> 01:03:18,820
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Mr. Buzzwell, we just passed three cups, and there's gallons more coming!

1003
01:03:18,890 --> 01:03:22,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}I think we need to shut down! Shut down? We've never shut down.

1004
01:03:23,830 --> 01:03:26,300
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Shut down honey production!

1005
01:03:26,360 --> 01:03:28,230
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Stop making honey!

1006
01:03:32,700 --> 01:03:34,230
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Turn your key, sir!

1007
01:03:45,850 --> 01:03:47,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}What do we do now?

1008
01:03:51,360 --> 01:03:53,020
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Cannonball!

1009
01:04:01,030 --> 01:04:02,900
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}We're shutting honey production!

1010
01:04:02,970 --> 01:04:04,130
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Mission abort.

1011
01:04:04,200 --> 01:04:07,690
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Aborting pollination and nectar detail. Returning to base.

1012
01:04:55,320 --> 01:04:58,220
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Adam, you wouldn't believe how much honey was out there.

1013
01:04:58,290 --> 01:04:59,280
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Oh yeah?

1014
01:04:59,360 --> 01:05:02,090
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}What's going on? Where is everybody?

1015
01:05:02,860 --> 01:05:05,350
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Are they out celebrating? They're home.

1016
01:05:05,430 --> 01:05:08,360
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}They don't know what to do. Laying out, sleeping in.

1017
01:05:08,430 --> 01:05:11,960
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}I heard your Uncle Oarl was on his way to San Antonio with a cricket.

1018
01:05:12,040 --> 01:05:13,530
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}At least we got our honey back.

1019
01:05:13,600 --> 01:05:16,510
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Sometimes I think, so what if humans liked our honey?

1020
01:05:16,570 --> 01:05:17,800
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Who wouldn't?

1021
01:05:17,880 --> 01:05:21,740
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}It's the greatest thing in the world! I was excited to be part of making it.

1022
01:05:23,450 --> 01:05:26,180
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}This was my new desk. This was my new job.

1023
01:05:26,250 --> 01:05:28,050
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}I wanted to do it really well.

1024
01:05:28,120 --> 01:05:29,450
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}And now...

1025
01:05:30,290 --> 01:05:31,950
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Now I can't.

1026
01:05:42,600 --> 01:05:45,070
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}I don't understand why they're not happy.

1027
01:05:45,140 --> 01:05:47,570
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}I thought their lives would be better!

1028
01:05:47,640 --> 01:05:51,510
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}They're doing nothing. It's amazing. Honey really changes people.

1029
01:05:51,580 --> 01:05:54,640
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}You don't have any idea what's going on, do you?

1030
01:05:54,710 --> 01:05:57,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}What did you want to show me? This.

1031
01:05:59,380 --> 01:06:00,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}What happened here?

1032
01:06:00,750 --> 01:06:03,480
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}That is not the half of it.

1033
01:06:09,160 --> 01:06:11,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Oh, no. Oh, my.

1034
01:06:12,160 --> 01:06:14,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}They're all wilting.

1035
01:06:14,100 --> 01:06:16,190
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Doesn't look very good, does it?

1036
01:06:16,270 --> 01:06:17,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}No.

1037
01:06:17,670 --> 01:06:21,000
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}And whose fault do you think that is?

1038
01:06:23,010 --> 01:06:24,670
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}You know, I'm gonna guess bees.

1039
01:06:24,740 --> 01:06:25,940
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Bees?

1040
01:06:26,010 --> 01:06:27,940
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Specifically, me.

1041
01:06:28,010 --> 01:06:32,210
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}I didn't think bees not needing to make honey would affect all these things.

1042
01:06:32,280 --> 01:06:37,280
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}It's not just flowers. Fruits, vegetables, they all need bees.

1043
01:06:37,350 --> 01:06:40,220
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}That's our whole SAT test right there.

1044
01:06:40,290 --> 01:06:43,850
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Take away produce, that affects the entire animal kingdom.

1045
01:06:43,930 --> 01:06:45,360
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}And then, of course...

1046
01:06:45,430 --> 01:06:47,190
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}The human species?

