01:07:59,440 --> 01:08:02,770
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Wait a minute. Roses. Roses?

1065
01:08:03,270 --> 01:08:04,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Roses!

1066
01:08:05,440 --> 01:08:07,270
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Vanessa!

1067
01:08:07,950 --> 01:08:09,610
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Roses? !

1068
01:08:09,680 --> 01:08:11,080
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Barry?

1069
01:08:11,150 --> 01:08:14,210
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Roses are flowers! Yes, they are.

1070
01:08:14,290 --> 01:08:17,310
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Flowers, bees, pollen!

1071
01:08:17,390 --> 01:08:20,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}I know. That's why this is the last parade.

1072
01:08:20,790 --> 01:08:24,850
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Maybe not. Could you ask him to slow down?

1073
01:08:24,930 --> 01:08:26,520
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Could you slow down?

1074
01:08:29,170 --> 01:08:30,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}Barry!

1075
01:08:30,830 --> 01:08:34,330
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\3c&H000000&\i1}OK, I made a huge mistake. This is a total disaster, all my fault.

